# Accessibility (WCAG AA)

## Semantic HTML

Use `<nav>`, `<main>`, `<footer>`, `<button>`, etc. Meaningful link text — not "click here".

## ARIA

- Icon-only buttons: `aria-label="Close menu"`
- Expandables: `aria-expanded`
- Dynamic updates: `aria-live="polite"`
- Decorative icons: `aria-hidden="true"`

## Keyboard and focus

- All interactive elements keyboard accessible
- Trap focus in modals/menus; restore focus on close
- `:focus-visible` for keyboard focus indicators
- Escape closes modals/menus
- Skip links for main content

## Forms and media

- All inputs have associated labels
- Images need meaningful `alt` text
- Use `sr-only` for screen-reader-only text

```tsx
useEffect(() => {
  const handleEscape = (e: KeyboardEvent) => {
    if (e.key === "Escape" && isOpen) onClose()
  }
  document.addEventListener("keydown", handleEscape)
  return () => document.removeEventListener("keydown", handleEscape)
}, [isOpen, onClose])
```
